Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum hit a game-winning 29-foot shot at the buzzer to lift the Celtics past the Raptors in overtime.
The Celtics won the game 126-123 in overtime.
RJ Barrett recorded his first triple-double with a career-best 13 assists.
Jakob Poeltl scored a career-best 35 points.
Post-Match Reflections: Jayson Tatum spoke about his buzzer-beating overtime 3-pointer, saying 'It felt good.'
Al Horford thanked Tatum for helping the Celtics avoid a second overtime period.
Jayson Tatum reflected on his missed shots in the second half, stating 'I missed so many shots in the second half, I was bound to hit one.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors forced the Celtics to overtime in Boston on the second night of a back-to-back.
The Raptors remain winless on the road with a 2-12 record and have lost 7 straight games.
The Celtics improved to an 11-3 record.
